INSERT INTO `dspt_history` VALUES (429,223,6,NULL,NULL,'NEW',NULL,NULL,NULL),(430,223,6,'Hi Melvin,\r\n\r\nWe were able to call back the customer already and confirmed as why she would like to discontinue the installation of MioTv. As per the customer she  spoke with her husband already about miotv and decided not to continue because they have starhub already and claiming that they have the same program specially Chinese channel that they usually watch, we tried to win back the customer and explained that she can have both starhub and miotv because it co exist and since she is interested also with but still she’s not interested at the moment and will just call back if ever she would like or decided to have miotv then. \r\n\r\nCustomer would like to have an assurance also that she will not be charge for discontinuing the installation of miotv. Customer’s schedule of installation will be on the 7th of Oct. \r\n\r\n\r\nGermaine – Please assist us to cancel the installation schedule for this customer.\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks,','Request to confirmation team for cancellation','PENDING','',NULL,'2011-09-28 18:44:11'),(431,223,6,'Hi Melvin / Arthur,\r\n\r\nDone.  We did not sign the cust up for the package. \r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\nJason\r\n\r\nFrom: Kwong Jie Hui Melvin On Behalf Of mioTV Teles(con)\r\nSent: Wednesday, September 28, 2011 2:21 PM\r\nTo: Mei Tong; arthur layos\r\nCc: \'Zardad Zardadal\'; Linda Ling; \'Joy Arenas\'\r\nSubject: RE: cancellation before crd- IC: S7776594H\r\n\r\nHi Jason,\r\n\r\nFYNA.\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\nHi Arthur,\r\n\r\nJust to inform you, Germaine is not with us anymore.\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\nMelvin Kwong','Jason Cancelled the Installation schedule.','RESOLVED','Case closed!',NULL,'2011-09-28 18:45:45'),(432,224,6,NULL,NULL,'NEW',NULL,NULL,NULL),(433,224,6,'From: Joy Arenas [mailto:joy@outsource2northstar.com] \r\nSent: Monday, September 26, 2011 1:44 PM\r\nTo: \'mioTV Teles(con)\'; \'arthur layos\'\r\nCc: \'Hu Yue Qing\'; \'Teh Jin Hui\'\r\nSubject: RE: DH0926007 - RE: MIO TV SALES ESCALATION S1752734G/Contact # D2566\r\n\r\nHi Nicole,\r\n\r\nHere’s my findings on the issue:\r\n\r\n\r\nCustomer’s claim:\r\n\r\nCustomer mentioned that was promised 6mnths foc viewing of all channels\r\n\r\nFindings based on Call transcription:\r\n\r\nAgent: You are given $4 rebate for this promotion and as part of the promotion, the installation is free for you, ok?\r\nCustomer: Until when the promotion?\r\nAgent: The promotion ma\'am will run for 6mos and you just need to spend $9.90 per month, ok for your MIO TV service \r\nCustomer: Every month I need to pay $9?\r\nAgent: $9 and .90c however like I\'ve mentioned, you  are given $4 rebate so it will reduced to $5.90 each month consumable.\r\n\r\nAgent: So ma\'am on your 1st month, you can have all the 56 channels and that includes 20 family channels, english entertainment, chinese, malay and indian channels.. And then for your second - 6th month, you can have the 20 family channels w/c includes news, documentary, entertainment and kids channels at the same price of $5.90 for each month for 6mos... \r\n\r\nVerbal agreement was ok, mentioned preview 56 channels on 1st month and 20 family channels on 2nd-6th month. Monthly charge of $9.90/month was mentioned less $4 rebate.\r\n\r\nBased on the conversation, staff did a good job in the explaining to the customer the details of the promotion in contrary to what the customer is claiming. \r\n\r\nI was able to callback the customer today. I gave her a quick recap of the deal and agreement she had with our staff that on the 1st month, she was told she can see 56 channels, 2nd-6th month, 20 family channels and need to pay $9.90 and with the rebate she only need to pay $5.90. However, customer seem forgot about it and believed on what she is claiming and mentioned she doesn’t want to hear anymore rubbish from us. I advised the customer to call 1688 and ask for the recording so she can be assured she was not misled.  Customer mentioned she wants to cancel MIO TV service and I told her about the ETC and again she claimed, she wasn’t informed about it. I suggested her to cancel after 6mos so not to pay the ETC. Based on the call, all the details the customer need to know was discussed by the staff. Customer hung up on me and is not picking up my call as I try to callback.\r\n\r\nAttached is the recording for your reference.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n\r\n\r\nJoy L. Arenas\r\nTeam Leader','','PENDING','',NULL,'2011-09-28 18:50:13'),(434,224,6,'Hi Joy,\r\n\r\nWill keep you informed if anything required.\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\nMelvin Kwong','From: Joy Arenas [mailto:joy@outsource2northstar.com] \r\nSent: Tuesday, September 27, 2011 2:48 PM\r\nTo: \'Joy Arenas\'; mioTV Teles(con); \'arthur layos\'\r\nCc: \'Hu Yue Qing\'; \'Teh Jin Hui\'\r\nSubject: RE: DH0926007 - RE: MIO TV SALES ESCALATION S1752734G/Contact # D2566\r\n\r\nHi Melvin,\r\n\r\nAlso for this case Melvin, I’d like to confirm if this is a closed case on our end? \r\n\r\nShould there be anything else we need to do for this case, please let us know. ?','RESOLVED','CASE CLOSED!',NULL,'2011-09-28 18:51:27'),(435,225,6,NULL,NULL,'NEW',NULL,NULL,NULL),(436,225,6,'We’ve listened to the call prior calling back the customer , Our agent spoke with the wife of the account holder. The agent discussed the MIO TV service for 6 months contract. He discussed the $4. rebate. The customer mentioned that she has Starhub, the agent said not to worry that both MIO TV service and Starhub can co-exist. The agent mentioned that installation is free for the MIO TV. The agent also discussed the price of the service within the 6 months and the price after 6 months. There were instances where the customer had difficulty understanding the agent and asked if he could speak Chinese. The agent tried to spell the word/s that the customer has difficulty understanding. The agent also asked the customer if she had pen and paper to write the important details down. The agent again mentioned that the installation is free. The agent asked what channels the customer preferred to watch. When the customer said Chinese channels the agent was about to discuss the Chinese offer when the customer said that she is about to leave. The agent said that he is almost done and just wanted to discuss to make it clear to the customer. He tried to discuss the Jingxuan pack (50% off for first 6 months) when the customer wasn’t interested with the promo the agent then went back to offering MIO TV for 6 months contract. The agent also mentioned the channels that the customer can have with the service. On the first month 56 channels including the family channels. The customer again mentioned that she had difficulty understanding what the agent is saying. \r\nThe agent explained that the monthly subscription is $9.90 but with the $4. so the customer would only pay $5.90/month for 6 months. On the 7th month onwards the customer would pay for $9.90 for the service.  \r\n(20:32) Agent: on your first month with the promotion the monthly subscription fee would only be $9.90. Can you please write this down.\r\nCustomer: $9.90\r\nAgent: Remember that we are giving you $4./monthly rebate for 6 months, you minus the $4. on $9.90. How much…\r\nCustomer: $5.90\r\nAgent: exactly, you would only be paying $5.90 every month for the first 6 months.\r\nCustomer: for the first 6 months.\r\nAgent: That’s correct. \r\nCustomer: yeah\r\n\r\nThe agent mentioned the channels that the customer can have on the first month, 56 channels and on the second month onwards 20 family channels.  The agent verified the installation address. Asked if there is an alarm system, the customer asked why the agent was asking this question. The agent replied that the reason he is asking this question is to make sure that the MIO TV that would be installed will not interfere with her alarm system. The agent also asked the distance of phone socket to TV. \r\nThe agent asked the customer to state the name and NRIC for the Verbal Agreement and prior giving the NRIC number, conversation went on pause and wife translating the information to her husband and after that Mrs. Phua stated the NRIC # of the subscriber, which is the husband (PHUA HIM KO- S0109540D). \r\n\r\nThe agent was going through the terms and conditions when the customer said that she has to go. The agent said that he is almost done and continued with the terms and conditions. The agent asked if the customer understood, agree and accept the terms and conditions. The customer gave affirmative response. The agent asked for a mobile number where she could be reached.The agent initially looked for the account holder PHUA HIM KO, the customer that answered the phone asked why the agent was looking for him. The agent then asked if she was Mrs. Phua when the customer said yes the agent proceeded with the conversation.  There were instances in the call where the agent and the customer had difficulty understanding each other. The customer had difficulty with English and would sometimes speak what sounded like Chinese. The agent patiently tried to explain the offers to the customer and even asked her to write things down to make it clear. From the transcription above, on 20:32 of the call the agent was able to mention the price for the MIO TV service for the applicable months. The agent should have tried to ask the secondary contact if she is authorized to subscribe for the MIO TV service. \r\n\r\n\r\nWe were able to call back today and spoke with Ms Eng wife of MR PHUA HIM KO, the account holder, as per the customer she would like to cancel the miotv service because they have starhub already and don’t want to pay extra for the miotv service. \r\n\r\nWe explained that even if they already have starhub they can still use miotv service for only $5.90 per month after the $4 rebate. But still Ms Eng don’t want to pay extra, so we explained also that if she will cancel the service and it’s still under promotion there is a charge of $68 for the use of the modem. But Ms Eng keep on saying she don’t want to pay and didn’t mind what we are trying to explain then she hung up.\r\n\r\nWe tried to call her back for the 2nd time still same reaction and simply hung up the phone.','a . We’ve listened to the call prior calling back the customer \r\n\r\nb. Callback the customer\r\n\r\nc. Then Email client on outcome of the call','PENDING','* Forwarded recording to the client',NULL,'2011-09-28 21:28:12'),(437,225,6,'Hi Arthur \r\n\r\nWill do so, will review the call tmr as I\'m out of the office. Thanx again for providing the review. If there is any requirement we will contact you again. \r\n\r\nSent from my iPhone\r\n\r\nOn Sep 27, 2011, at 20:41, \"arthur layos\" <arthur@outsource2northstar.com> wrote:\r\n\r\n> \r\n> Hi Jason,\r\n> \r\n> As I review of the call callback made today it was not mentioned that \r\n> the authorization is the issue, Mrs. Phoa just stated that she wants \r\n> to terminate the service because she has Starhub and they don\'t have \r\n> money to pay and don\'t want MIOTV anymore and no reason was given and \r\n> she just hang up.\r\n> \r\n> During the call presentation of staff when our staff made the sale, \r\n> prior giving the NRIC number Mrs. Phua talked to Mr. Phua and it was \r\n> heard in the background that she was translating what the offer of \r\n> MIOTV, after a long paused Mrs. Phua gave the NRIC number to the agent \r\n> then proceeded to the VA part.\r\n> \r\n> The Staff was assumptive to continue the sales call since Mrs Phua \r\n> translated the offer to Mr. Phua and have the confidence that Mr Phua \r\n> has the knowledge of what  Mrs. Phua have signed up since she gave Mr. \r\n> Phua\'s NRIC #, my two cents.\r\n> \r\n> I recommend someone should listen to the call and give us feedback for \r\n> training and development.\r\n> \r\n> \r\n> \r\n> Arthur Nicole Layos\r\n> Campaign Manager\r\n> \r\n> Northstar Solutions, Inc.\r\n> US TFN: 